/*
The number, a, is given and it is required that a is prime.
The function, prime_sieve, is called to generate a prime sieve and
returns an array of primes.

The function, factor(n), is called to generate the prime factors of n.

The function, factor_sum, is called to sum the prime factors of n.

>>> prime_sieve(20)
[2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]
>>> factor(20)
[2, 3, 5, 7, 11, 13, 17, 19]
>>> factor_sum(20)
